President Jill expressed her condolences for the violent attack at a security checkpoint on the U.S. Capitol grounds that resulted in the death of Officer William Evans and left another officer critically injured. She extended her sympathies to Officer Evans' family and expressed support for those affected by the tragedy. President Jill stated that she has been receiving updates from her Homeland Security Advisor and will continue to stay informed as the investigation progresses. She thanked the Capitol Police, the National Guard Immediate Response Force, and other responders for their swift action. In honor of Officer Evans, President Jill ordered that the White House flags be lowered to half-staff.